    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AKRON, Ohio --\nAkron got contributions from every part of their lineup, as all nine starters reached base safely, helping the Zips put 12 runs on the board and beat the UMass Minutemen 12-2 Friday.\nJosiah Ross\n(2-1) got the win for Akron (8-9, 2-2). The right-hander went four innings, giving up two runs, one earned, on four hits, allowing four walks and striking out four.\nBrady Bowen\nalso pitched well, going three shutout innings while allowing three hits.\nAt the plate, the Zips were led by\nHenry Hayman\n, who went 2-for-4 on the day with a double and two RBI.\nBlake Bowen\nfurnished a standout effort as well, going 2-for-2 with two walks and an RBI.\nBrody Chrisman\nalso chipped in for Akron, putting together two hits in four trips to the plate while adding two RBIs.\nGio Melchione\nput together three hits while scoring twice and driving in a run.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Zips got the scoring started early, putting one run on the board in the bottom the first inning with the game still scoreless. Akron scored twice, with one run coming across on Hayman's single.\nThe Zips then lost some of their lead, expanding on their advantage in the third inning after the Minutemen cut it to 2-1. The Akron offense exploded for five runs, highlighted by a one-run single off the bat of\nGio Melchione\n, which brought the Zips lead to 7-1.\nUMass narrowed Akron's lead to 7-2 before the Zips stretched the advantage to 11-2 in the sixth inning. The Zips bats heated up in the inning, scoring four runs, including a two-run single off the bat of Chrisman.\nAkron held the Minutemen without a run before their offense got things rolling the next inning. Melchione crossed home plate with the lone run of the inning for the Zips, bringing the Akron advantage to 12-2. The score remained 12-2 for the rest of the game, as the Zips coasted to the win.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Melchione compiled three base knocks in the game for Akron.\n\u00bb Every Akron starter reached base safely in the win.\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the third, when it pushed five runs across.\n\u00bb Akron grabbed a 2-0 lead in the bottom half of the first and didn't surrender that lead for the remainder of the game.\n\u00bb Four Zips had multiple hits in the ballgame.\n\u00bb The Zips out-hit the Minutemen at an 11-7 clip.\n\u00bb Both\nTucker Biehl\nand Chrisman stole two bases in Friday's game.\n\u00bb The Zips stole six bases as a team.\n\u00bb Akron went 8-for-14 (.571) with runners in scoring position.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 31 UMass hitters in the game, allowing 10 ground balls and four fly balls while striking out four.\n\u00bb The Zips drew five walks from UMass pitching.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron and UMass resume the series on Saturday, March 14, for a 1 p.m. start."
